<Issue id="17336" key="STL-328" number="328" project="10001" reporter="delventhalz" assignee="alexanderzhovnuvaty" creator="delventhalz" type="10004" summary="CLI produces stack trace when specifying url without scheme" priority="4" resolution="10000" status="10001" created="2017-05-31 18:56:04.0" updated="2021-03-15 19:01:50.0" resolutiondate="2021-03-15 19:01:38.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="17340"> <description><! CDATA When calling the sawtooth CLI using a URL without a scheme, for example:  {{sawtooth block list --url localhost:8080}}     An awful error message and stack trace is produced:  {{}}{{}}{{requests.exceptions.InvalidSchema: No connection adapters were found for 'localhost:8080/blocks'}}     The reason is the omission of the http(s) scheme from the beginning of the URL. It may be convenient to default to _"http://"_ if no scheme is input, but either away, when there is a bad URL, this error should be caught, and a more sensible _CLIError_ raised.  ></description> </Issue>
